de.mrapp.android.validation.validators.text

Class LetterOrNumberValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.mrapp.android.validation.validators.AbstractValidator<java.lang.CharSequence>
      • de.mrapp.android.validation.validators.text.LetterOrNumberValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Validator<java.lang.CharSequence>

    public class LetterOrNumberValidator
extends AbstractValidator<java.lang.CharSequence>
    A validator, which allows to validate texts to ensure, that they only contain letters or numbers. It is possible to specify, whether only uppercase or lowercase letters should be accepted, or if they should be threatened case-insensitive. Letters are considered to be all alphabetical characters from A to B. Additionally, it is possible to specify whether spaces should be allowed and to add special characters, which should also be accepted. Empty texts are also accepted.
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Michael Rapp
